<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>PlentyTestPlugin – Demo Homepage</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <style>
        body {
            margin: 0;
            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
            background: #f4f4f4;
            color: #222;
        }
        header {
            background: #1c2b39;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 24px 40px;
        }
        header h1 {
            margin: 0;
            font-size: 22px;
        }
        header span {
            font-size: 13px;
            color: #9fb3c8;
        }
        main {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 40px auto;
            background: #fff;
            padding: 32px 40px;
            border-radius: 6px;
            box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }
        main h2 {
            margin-top: 0;
        }
        .badge {
            display: inline-block;
            background: #ffb400;
            color: #1c2b39;
            font-weight: bold;
            font-size: 12px;
            padding: 4px 10px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
        }
        footer {
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
            font-size: 12px;
            color: #888;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>PlentyTestPlugin</h1>
        <span>Demo homepage override — hardcoded content, no live data</span>
    </header>

    <main>
        <div class="badge">TEST PLUGIN</div>
        <h2>This is a hardcoded demo page</h2>
        <p>
            This page is rendered by <strong>PlentyTestPlugin</strong> and replaces
            the normal PlentyONE storefront homepage (the <code>/</code> route).
            All content on this page is static — nothing here comes from the
            shop's actual categories, items, or CMS content.
        </p>
        <p>
            Use this as a starting point: swap this Twig template's markup for
            whatever you actually want the homepage to show, or replace the
            static HTML with real Twig variables/data providers once you're
            ready to go beyond a demo.
        </p>
    </main>

    <footer>
        PlentyTestPlugin demo &middot; rendered from resources/views/content/demo-home.twig
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
